(84, 50, 'content_description_1', 'This portfolio is a demonstration of my ability to understand the content that was presented during my time in the Front End Web Development program at the Institute of British Columbia. I have used Rest API in React to retrieve data from WordPress, effectively using a Headless CMS to store all of the information that you see within the website.'),
(85, 50, '_content_description_1', 'field_640ba6c5413df'),
(86, 50, 'content_description_2', 'In the early stages, I wireframed the overall layout that I envisioned within the portfolio itself. I originally planned to include a section that featured my interests, though I felt that it is important to highlight my relatable value first, and then showcase my skills and passion in other areas.\r\n\r\nThe conceptual process began with a rough layout created in Adobe XD, which I would then use to structure the basis of how I wished to present the work that I did in an appropriate manner.'),
(87, 50, '_content_description_2', 'field_640ba6d7413e0'),
(88, 50, 'image_2', '58'),
(89, 50, '_image_2', 'field_640ba6e5413e1'),
(90, 50, 'content_description_3', 'I went back and forth in what I felt was the strongest way to showcase my skills, as the main purpose of this portfolio is to highlight the areas of expertise in my capabilities. Therefore, I decided that beginning the website with an introductory section of myself was a good way to break the ice and create a more approachable section that reflects who I am - personable.'),
