(199, 50, 'content_description_4', 'As this was one of the last projects of the program, I have been accustomed to different software and tools to utilize within the development of the web portfolio. At the beginning of the timeline, Adobe XD was the program of choice for wireframing and exhibiting my ideas to my instructors. This was one of the early developmental parts that had me re-evaluate what I wanted the basis of this portfolio to consist of. I used the WordPress interface to handle custom fields and inputs, and added code to the WordPress files that determined the types of content that I wished to have on every respective page.\r\n\r\nAll of the back-end coding was done through Visual Studio Code, and Postman was used in helping to retrieve the API data from WordPress to display within the React development environment. Adobe Illustrator and Adobe Photoshop were used to edit site images, and GitHub was used to log changes and create a repository.\r\n'),
