(241, 50, 'problem', 'This portfolio is a demonstration of my ability to understand the content that was presented during my time in the Front End Web Development program at the Institute of British Columbia. I have used Rest API in React to retrieve data from WordPress, effectively using a Headless CMS to store all of the information that you see within the website.'),
(242, 50, '_problem', 'field_640ba6c5413df'),
(243, 50, 'tools_used', 'In the early stages, I wireframed the overall layout that I envisioned within the portfolio itself. I originally planned to include a section that featured my interests, though I felt that it is important to highlight my relatable value first, and then showcase my skills and passion in other areas.\r\n\r\nThe conceptual process began with a rough layout created in Adobe XD, which I would then use to structure the basis of how I wished to present the work that I did in an appropriate manner.'),
(244, 50, '_tools_used', 'field_640ba6d7413e0'),
(245, 50, 'inspiration', 'I went back and forth in what I felt was the strongest way to showcase my skills, as the main purpose of this portfolio is to highlight the areas of expertise in my capabilities. Therefore, I decided that beginning the website with an introductory section of myself was a good way to break the ice and create a more approachable section that reflects who I am - personable. I found great inspiration from several websites and essentially attempted to use those components in my own work. Websites that use colour and properly make use of transitions from one section to the next without losing the overall tone of the portfolio itself. If it works, it works; and this is what I considered as I moved forward with design decisions. There were several different websites that I found to use exciting and natural animations that are used in key areas that don\'t take away from the visitor\'s experience on the website itself.'),
(246, 50, '_inspiration', 'field_640ba6fb413e2'),
(247, 50, 'examples', 'As this was one of the last projects of the program, I have been accustomed to different software and tools to utilize within the development of the web portfolio. At the beginning of the timeline, Adobe XD was the program of choice for wireframing and exhibiting my ideas to my instructors. This was one of the early developmental parts that had me re-evaluate what I wanted the basis of this portfolio to consist of. I used the WordPress interface to handle custom fields and inputs, and added code to the WordPress files that determined the types of content that I wished to have on every respective page.\r\n\r\nAll of the back-end coding was done through Visual Studio Code, and Postman was used in helping to retrieve the API data from WordPress to display within the React development environment. Adobe Illustrator and Adobe Photoshop were used to edit site images, and GitHub was used to log changes and create a repository.\r\n'),
