(249, 50, 'final_result', 'I found great success in researching and preparing this web portfolio to summarize the main skills that I obtained in communicating with a headless CMS. I would like to build upon this portfolio and adjust it as I feel would better reflect my skills and capabilities; preferably showcasing my creativity through smooth animations and having the entire portfolio feel as though it flows smoothly within each section.'),
(250, 50, '_final_result', 'field_641761e03708e'),
(251, 50, 'tools_used_2', 'As this was one of the last projects of the program, I have been accustomed to different software and tools to utilize within the development of the web portfolio. At the beginning of the timeline, Adobe XD was the program of choice for wireframing and exhibiting my ideas to my instructors. This was one of the early developmental parts that had me re-evaluate what I wanted the basis of this portfolio to consist of. I used the WordPress interface to handle custom fields and inputs, and added code to the WordPress files that determined the types of content that I wished to have on every respective page.\r\n\r\nAll of the back-end coding was done through Visual Studio Code, and Postman was used in helping to retrieve the API data from WordPress to display within the React development environment. Adobe Illustrator and Adobe Photoshop were used to edit site images, and GitHub was used to log changes and create a repository.\r\n'),
(252, 50, '_tools_used_2', 'field_6417617337089'),
(253, 57, 'problem', 'In the FWD program at BCIT, I was tasked along with two other colleagues in creating a movie database which retrieves API information from themoviedatabase.com and utilizes it within the application. Essentially, the goal was to replicate our own rendition of a movie website that is fully functional and has the same functionality as a movie database website.'),
(254, 57, '_problem', 'field_640ba6c5413df'),
(255, 57, 'tools_used', 'This project was the first hands-on work that I did with React and the underlying framework that React has with SASS .css files. Visual Studio Code was used as the preferred program to incorporate the files with one another, and GitHub was used as the collaboration tool to upload and connect our work together. '),
(256, 57, '_tools_used', 'field_640ba6d7413e0'),
(257, 57, 'tools_used_2', 'Using React was a challenge for myself as I had only been introduced to the language several weeks prior, but I knew that it is a very popular framework and would be beneficial to learn. I wanted to use React as much as I could in my work and so I pushed myself to learn the fundamentals of the assigned task - which included grabbing an API endpoint - which further grew my understanding of the langauge.'),
(258, 57, '_tools_used_2', 'field_6417617337089'),
(259, 57, 'inspiration', 'When I began laying out the wireframes; which was the individual part of the process, I wanted to use my past skills in user experience to my advantage. I went to research the different websites that were similar to what I envisioned my end product to be. I considered usability, affordances (common elements or actions in layouts), and how I wanted to use those components for my own project. After several iterations I ended up deciding to develop my layout similar to that of Rotten Tomatoes; as I wished to incorporate as much white space as I could to \"clean up\" the interface and not clutter it with extra images. This, along with Rotten Tomatoes\' theme of primarily using one colour is what I felt to be the basis of a well-branded website.'),
(260, 57, '_inspiration', 'field_640ba6fb413e2'),
(261, 57, 'examples', 'IMDb is arguably one of the more popular movie information websites that is around, and that is where I found the layout of my website to gather components from. I used a darker colour for contrasting elements such as the header and footer, and used a single orange as the theme colour for the website. I also drew inspiration from the initial site that we were tasked with grabbing database information from (the movie database), and chose a colour palette that I felt best suited the \"feel\" that I wanted to have for the website. Rotten Tomatoes is another inspiration in terms of layout, careful use of colours, and proper spacing from which I gathered a fair deal of my design decisions from. The website\'s name Sunset Movies plays on the common evening-viewing hours of films as a way to relax, thus using an orange contrast to welcome the visitor to the website.'),
(262, 57, '_examples', 'field_641761ad3708c'),
(263, 57, 'final_result', 'Overall, my team members and I decided that I had a strong layout for a project and we proceeded to develop the website in React. This project gave me a much better understanding of translating developmental ideas, wireframes, and iterations into an end product that is functional and successfully retrieves data through an API. After completing this project, I was more confident in attempting to develop my web portfolio using React. I received positive feedback for the design and layout, and will continue to polish the project over time to have every link functional and to really give it more of a movie database feeling.'),
(264, 57, '_final_result', 'field_641761e03708e'),
(265, 59, 'problem', 'I was grouped with two colleagues and tasked with creating an ecommerce website that functions as a fictional cafe. Many of the challenges included creating fictional locations and mapping them using Google Maps API, writing functions to handle categorization on product pages, and implementing a filtering system for popular drinks as determined by the client through WordPress.'),
(266, 59, '_problem', 'field_640ba6c5413df'),
