(271, 59, 'tools_used', 'The tools that I used for this project were Visual Studio Code for project development and a GitHub repository for project management. These were the main technical tools that were were required, and the software that I used included WordPress, WooCommerce, and numerous plugins that aided the support and performance of the ecommerce site.'),
(272, 59, '_tools_used', 'field_640ba6d7413e0'),
(273, 59, 'tools_used_2', 'I aided in the research of successful websites related to the industry, which even included visiting some of these locations to get a better feel of how the branding for the website was done through the design of their store. Using this information, my colleagues and I developed a catalog of images to use that best portrayed modern cafes and carefully selected menu items that were appealing. This project was done using HTML5, PHP, WordPress, and WooCommerce.'),
(274, 59, '_tools_used_2', 'field_6417617337089'),
(275, 59, 'image_3', '102'),
(276, 59, '_image_3', 'field_6417614f37088'),
(277, 59, 'inspiration', 'Our team gathered inspiration from several different sources; most notably Cartem\'s Donuts and Mello. The colours of both of these websites was very appealing to us, we felt that each of these websites possessed important components which were beneficial to the experience of the site visitor. It was decided that branding BAM Cafe in the way that Mello uses its colours was effective, but felt Cartem\'s use of shading of a primary theme colour was a bold choice that makes an impact on its branding. Ultimately, we decided on two primary colours with accents of complementary colours allocated throughout the site.'),
(278, 59, '_inspiration', 'field_640ba6fb413e2'),
(279, 59, 'image_4', '105'),
(280, 59, '_image_4', 'field_641761893708a'),
(281, 59, 'image_5', '106'),
(282, 59, '_image_5', 'field_6417619d3708b'),
(283, 59, 'examples', 'When making decisions from a design perspective, it often came down to how things were looking. What was more challenging was the decision of creating a separate online menu and in-store shop menu, along with merchandise that would be sold. In this instance, using a foundational layout of organizing key highlighted areas into sections made the most sense as the visitor navigated throughout the website. This way, site visitors were able to choose to go to section after scrolling through the homepage first. Essentially, simplicity and affordances were the top components considered when making these decisions.'),
(284, 59, '_examples', 'field_641761ad3708c'),
(285, 59, 'image_6', '104'),
(286, 59, '_image_6', 'field_641761cc3708d'),
(287, 59, 'final_result', 'I was pleased with the result of this capstone project; from the beginning of the several status meetings I quickly began to understand how the developmental process works; and it prepared me for working with superiors and/or clients in the future. The website feels as though it is an existing business; a goal of mine going into the project. I wished to create work that mimics shops that are successful. I feel that BAM Cafe truly captured the identity we set out to achieve when first undertaking this challenge.'),
(288, 59, '_final_result', 'field_641761e03708e'),
